{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban button batteries from children\u2019s toys",
        "additional_details": "We trust that toys made for children are safe for them. But button batteries can be deadly, so we think they must be banned from these items.\r\n \r\nButton batteries are extremely dangerous if ingested by children and currently they are not banned from children\u2019s toys. While regulations state they must be secured, such as with screws, we do not think this is enough. Toys can be broken, giving children access to the batteries, or the compartments may not be replaced correctly due to human error, leaving the batteries easily accessible when the toy is handed back to the child. We feel that too many accidents can occur without a ban on using them in children\u2019s toys.",
        "background": "We think that all button batteries should be banned from being used in children\u2019s toys to prevent fatal and tragic accidents due to them being ingested.",
